Farmington Public Schools will hold a virtual School Board Meeting on Tuesday, September 8.

Due to the Coronavirus crisis, Farmington Public Schools will hold a virtual School Board Meeting on Tuesday, September 8, 2020.

The School Board meeting will begin at 6 p.m. School Board members and presenters will be using the WebEx meeting platform.

Please complete this form to submit a public comment. We will be accepting public comments until 4:00 p.m. on Tuesday, September 8. Your comments will be shared with the public and full Board by the Board President during the meeting under the Public Comment portion of the agenda.

The full agenda for the Board Meeting can be found on the District's website at www.farmington.k12.mi.us. Please tune in and watch the meeting LIVE on TV-10. It will also be live-streamed on the TV-10 Video on Demand site found on the District’s website.

Anyone needing special accommodations to participate should call Diane Bauman, Director, School/Community Relations, at 248.426.5000 and arrangements will be made.

post_text:
September 3, 2020

Dear FPS Middle School Families,

The purpose of this message is to provide an update to the status of our middle school athletic programming for the fall 2020 season. Farmington Public Schools’ middle schools are part of the Central Oakland Middle School Athletic Conference (COMSAC), and all of our contests for fall sports are within this conference. Recently, COMSAC has elected to cancel all fall middle school athletics. As such, Farmington Public Schools will not be having any school-based athletic programming this fall. While this is certainly disappointing, I am hopeful that we will be able to hold athletics for the remaining three seasons of the year.

If you have any questions, please feel free to contact me at jonathan.manier@fpsk12.net.

Sincerely,

Jon Manier
Director of Athletics
Farmington Public Schools

post_text:
During this Moving Forward Learning environment, parents are able to call the FPS-Oakland Schools Service Desk for technology support.

The Service Desk will not be taking calls directly from students, only from parents and guardians. Parents or guardians can grant approval for the service desk staff to speak directly to their child as long as the parent remains present during the entirety of the conversation.

It’s also important to note that the Service Desk can NOT provide passwords to parents/students over the phone. This information can be looked up in the MiStar Parent Portal - https://mistar.oakland.k12.mi.us/farmington/parentportal/

The following support method must be initiated by a parent/guardian or a staff member. A student is NOT allowed to contact the support desk directly.

Call the Service Desk at 248-209-2060 to speak to a representative Monday - Friday from 7:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.

Oakland School Service Desk | Supporting Farmington Public Schools

post_text:
National School Lunch Free/Reduced Applications

A new meal application must be completed every school year. New applications for free/reduced lunches are now available online at www.lunchapp.com. Submitting your application electronically is the quickest and most efficient way to get your application in. Printable copies are available on the District website under the Nutrition Services link if you are unable to complete the application online. Paper applications may be mailed to East Middle Schools, c/o Nutrition Services Department, 25000 Middlebelt, Farmington Hills, MI 48306 or faxed to (248) 489-3745.

Please allow 10 working days for processing of applications.
Payments for meals are required until receiving approval of the program.

If you have any questions, please contact Patti Carden at patti.carden@fpsk12.net or at 248-489-3717.

Photography and Visual Art winners from the Farmington Public School District’s PTA Reflections program will be on display in the lower level atrium at Farmington Hills City
Hall through September 2, 2020. The 32 pieces from elementary, middle, and high school levels on exhibit reflect this year’s “Look Within” theme.

The public is welcome to view the work during regular business hours, Monday through Friday from 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. at Farmington Hills City Hall located at 31555 W. Eleven Mile Road at the corner of Orchard Lake Road.

The artwork displayed at Farmington Hills City Hall is a small sample of the entries that advanced from their individual school level competition to compete at the Farmington District level. Congratulations!!! #FPSSuccess

post_text:
Update on the Virtual Learning Path (VLP) for K-5 students

As a result of the Board of Education approval of the Moving Forward Learning Plan, FPS will begin the year with Learning at a Distance.

All K-5 students will enter Learning at a Distance and the Virtual Learning Path is suspended during this time.

In the event there is a phase-in of in-person learning, families will be able to elect to stay remote through the Virtual Learning Path.

K-5 families do not need to make a decision at this time about whether they will enter the Virtual Learning Path at the start of the school year. We will continue to communicate to families regarding the timeline and choices related to the Virtual Learning Path.

Thank you.

post_text:
The Board of Education voted 5-2 to start the 2020-2021 school year remotely.

The Board of Education approved the following recommendation in a 5-2 vote:

Start the 2020-21 school year (for all K-12 students) in Learning at a Distance (fully remote).

Learning at a Distance (fully remote) will be in place for all students K-12 at least through October 30, 2020.

K-5 VLP paused during this time.

Board will continue to revisit the timeline based on conditions.

Planning will continue to take place to phase-in face-to-face instruction for certain populations after October 30th, as appropriate.

#FPSbettertogether

post_text: Did you miss our summer tryout? It's not too late! Join us on September 12 & 13 and help grow our pompon family. Our team is open to all incoming 9th-12th graders at Farmington and North Farmington High School for the 2020-2021 school year. Our tryouts will be held in person, with numerous safety protocols in place to combat the transmission of possible COVID-19. We have a safe practice plan put in place that is available to all current and interested members of our team! There is an option for a video tryout upon request! Our season is off to a great start, and we cannot wait to grow our team! If you are interested, please use the link below to fill out a google form and be added to our email list to receive more information! post_text:
Farmington Public Schools has released the official school district calendar for the 2020-2021 school year.

The first day of school is a half-day and will be held on Monday, August 31, 2020.

The new calendar provides flexibility during the week before students start school for teachers to complete “meet and greets” and reviews of safety procedures.

A few important things to note:
-The calendar reflects a Pre-Labor Day start date which is new for the District.
-Winter Vacation will be two full weeks in length.
-February Break and Spring Recess are both one week in length.
-Per the Oakland Schools’ Common Calendar, Spring Recess is in conjunction with Easter Sunday.
-The last day of school will be held on Friday, June 11, 2021.

The calendar is subject to changes and additions, as necessary, and will be modified on the District website.
The calendar is now available, both online and printable versions, on our website at www.farmington.k12.mi.us/calendars.

We look forward to a great year in Farmington Public Schools.

Farmington Public Schools has released the official school district calendar for the 2020-2021 school year.

The first day of school is a half-day and will be held on Monday, August 31, 2020.

The new calendar provides flexibility during the week before students start school for teachers to complete “meet and greets” and reviews of safety procedures.

A few important things to note:
-The calendar reflects a Pre-Labor Day start date which is new for the District.
-Winter Vacation will be two full weeks in length.
-February Break and Spring Recess are both one week in length.
-Per the Oakland Schools’ Common Calendar, Spring Recess is in conjunction with Easter Sunday.
-The last day of school will be held on Friday, June 11, 2021.

The calendar is subject to changes and additions, as necessary, and will be modified on the District website.
The calendar is now available, both online and printable versions, on our website at www.farmington.k12.mi.us/calendars.

We look forward to a great year in Farmington Public Schools.

Farmington Public Schools is thankful for community support.

Several local companies have been generous enough to support Farmington Public Schools in its efforts to support children during the COVID-19 pandemic. The following companies have donated items or monies toward keeping our staff safe and most importantly, feeding our families:

• $3,000 - Matarne North America, a MOM Group company - Donated GoGo Squeez Applesauce.
• $3,000 - Dechen Consulting Group, Inc. - Applied towards community meals and employee Personal Protection Equipment (PPE).
• $603.55 - Community Choice Credit Union - Paid off negative meal balances.
• $200 Bob & Cherie Seidl - Applied towards community meals.

Farmington Public Schools is grateful for those that have donated. The District is dedicated to assisting our families in any way possible during these difficult times.

Thank you, Matarne North America, Dechen Consulting Group Inc., Community Choice Credit Union, and Bob & Cherie Seidl! Dechen Consulting Group, Inc., & Community Choice Credit Union

Community Food Pantry - Saturday, July 18

The Tawheed Center of Farmington Hills, together
with Muslim Family Services, will host a mobile food
pantry on the third Saturday of each month. The
food pantry is open to all low- to no-income families
and individuals in the community who are in need.
The next pantry is scheduled from 11 a.m. - 1 p.m.
on Saturday, July 18.

The food pantry takes place at the Tawheed Center of Farmington Hills,29707 W. 10 Mile Road. In the present environment, pre-packaged boxes of food will be provided curbside at the Tawheed Center. For more information,
please call 248-252-6962.

Interested in joining the Farmington United Varsity Pompon team? Come meet our coaches and tryout next weekend, July 10th & 11th at the Farmington High School Athletic Field.

Our team is open to all incoming 9th-12th graders at Farmington High School, North Farmington High School and Farmington Central High School and there is no experience needed!

The first day will be a clinic teaching basic pom skill and learning your tryout routine, and the second day you will perform the routine and special skills to our judges. There will also be a mandatory parent Zoom meeting at 8PM on July 10th. If you are in need of a video submission tryout, please contact our head coach at walshde@mail.gvsu.edu.

If you plan to attend our tryouts, please contact the head coach at walshde@mail.gvsu.edu!

Our safe practice plan will be included in that email, as well as extremely important information on special guidelines we will be following and requiring our potential team members to follow during tryouts. We can't wait to see you there!

post_text:
June 12, 2020

Good Evening FPS Families,

As we close the 2019-2020 school year, we wanted to reach out and get some feedback on both the Continuity of Learning Plan that guided instruction at the end of this year, as well as your thoughts about what next year’s school year may look like.

Your feedback is so valuable and will inform our planning for the fall. We appreciate your commitment and partnership with FPS and truly value your feedback. We are asking if you could complete the survey by Tuesday, June 16 by 11 p.m.

As always, if you have any questions, please send them to info@fpsk12.net and someone will get back to you.

In closing, we wish you a wonderful, relaxing summer. Thank you for all of the support you have given us as we moved through these uncharted waters together.

Elementary

https://forms.gle/B96HNUAJvPCLtBWp7

Secondary

https://forms.gle/4g4h78b871nk14kUA

post_text: Congratulations, Caleb! #FPSSuccess #FPSbettertogether
shared_text:
FCB - Farmington Community Band
June 8 at 10:26 AM ·

Caleb LaBelle Recieves FCB Scholarship

On May 29th Farmington High School Graduate Caleb LaBelle was presented with the first George and Murilla Berryman Music Scholarship award at his home in Farmington. Caleb has been a student member of the FCB for 2 years and plans to attend the University of Michigan in the fall. He plans to use the scholarship award to purchase a new clarinet.

Congratulations, Caleb! #FPSSuccess #FPSbettertogether

post_text: CARES of Farmington Hills will host a May 29 free drive-thru food distribution for area families with children. The food distribution, open from 3 p.m. to 6 p.m., is sponsored by Gleaners Community Food Bank. No appointment is needed, and guests do not need to be registered with CARES. Participants should remain in their vehicles as volunteers put the groceries in the trunk. If you walk up, be prepared to carry or cart away 20-30 pounds of groceries. CARES is located at 27835 Shiawassee Road.

post_text:
Stifel anticipates pricing the week of May 25, $58,840,000 in tax-exempt bonds for Farmington Public Schools

Stifel, Nicolaus & Company, Incorporated anticipates pricing the week of May 25, 2020 the following tax-exempt bonds for Farmington Public Schools - 2020 School Building and Site Bonds (Unlimited Tax General Obligation).

Interest on the Tax-Exempt bonds will be free from federal and Michigan state income taxes.
These bonds are anticipated to be rated Aa3 by Moody’s.
This announcement is neither an offer to sell nor a solicitation of an offer to buy any of these securities. Any offer to sell will be made pursuant to the final official statement.

For a preliminary official statement and more information, please call: 844. 877. 1322.

To view the offering, visit https://www.munios.com/munios-notice.aspx?i=TCDV5ETS81U2

To learn more about Farmington Public Schools, visit www.farmington.k12.mi.us.

post_text:
We wish everyone a relaxing Memorial Day Weekend. Please take time to honor our veterans during this weekend. 2020 Virtual Memorial Day Parade: In the interest of public health and safety, and in compliance with State Executive Orders, the Farmington Memorial Day Parade will not take place this year. The Groves Walker American Legion Post 346 and the Xemplar Club of Farmington/Farmington Hills have cancelled the Memorial Day event to help reduce the risk of spreading the coronavirus.

The Parade Committee has put together a Virtual Memorial Day Parade video including footage and messages from the 2019 parade and participants. The video will be available on the parade website Memorial Day weekend.

The public is invited to send a message of thanks and support to our local veterans and their families, first responders and front line workers at www.memorialdayparade.us.

The Groves Walker American Legion Post 346 and the Xemplar Club of Farmington/Farmington Hills have cancelled the Memorial Day event to help reduce the risk of spreading the coronavirus.

The Parade Committee has put together a Virtual Memorial Day Parade video including footage and messages from the 2019 parade and participants. The video will be available on the parade web site on Memorial Day weekend. The public is invited to send a message of thanks and support to our local veterans and their families, first responders and front line workers at www.memorialdayparade.us.

#caringcommunity

Farmington Public Schools' Nutrition Services is proud to announce a partnership with the USDA Farmers to Families Food Box Program to provide fresh and wholesome food to our families!

This is open to all household members regardless of age!

You can pick up a fresh vegetable box, fresh fruit box and dairy box* at East Middle School, 25000 Middlebelt Rd., Farmington Hills or North Farmington High School, 32900 W. 13 Mile Rd., Farmington Hills every Wednesday, starting on May 20 through June 24. Distribution will start at 11 a.m. – 1 p.m. The program runs at the same time as the student meal pick ups.

*Box availability may vary each week.

#FPSSuccess #FPSbettertogether

post_text:
Due to the Coronavirus Crisis resulting in a Stay-at-Home order, the Farmington Public Schools’ Dance Company Audition modified process can be found here.

Dance Company Audition Process:
1. Review and Learn Four Essential Exercises.
2. Record yourself performing each exercise. The video must capture the full length of your body.
3. Upload each of your (4) videos to Google or Youtube, and an optional 5th video of your 2.5-minute solo in any dance style.
4. Begin the Audition/Application now through Friday, May 22, 2020.

Students seeking placement in Dance 2/Dance 3 will use the same audition process, but will:
1. Review and Learn Five Basic Exercises to demonstrate an ability to execute fundamental skills beyond the Dance 1 level.
2. Record yourself performing each exercise. The video must capture the full length of your body.
3. Upload each of your (5) videos to Google or Youtube.
4. Begin the Audition/Application now through Friday, May 22, 2020.

Questions? Please contact Mrs. Banks at tumija.banks@fpsk12.net

Teacher of the Year - Farmington

The Suburban Collection is at Suburban Nissan of Farmington Hills (37901 Grand River Ave, Farmington Hills, MI).
May 7 at 1:04 PM · Farmington Hills, MI ·

Mrs. Pinter is the Farmington Public Schools Teacher of the Year, and with this being Teacher Appreciation Week 🎓, we thought a video about the moment she found out and that she got a FREE CAR would be priceless.

Before we all started learning from home, we had the chance to surprise and celebrate Mrs. Pinter at Forest Elementary School. Please watch and share this week as it’s even more important now to celebrate our teachers as they continue to do their incredible work in a new way.

post_text:
CARES of Farmington Hills will host a May 1 free mobile food distribution for area families with children.

The food distribution, open from 3 p.m. to 6 p.m., is sponsored by Gleaners Community Food Bank. No appointment is needed, and guests do not need to be registered with CARES.

Participants should remain in their vehicles as volunteers put the groceries in the trunk. If you walk up, be prepared to carry or cart away 20-30 pounds of groceries.

CARES is located at 27835 Shiawassee Road. To learn more, visit caresfh.org

post_text: Did you know that Wednesday, April 22 is Earth Day? Mr. V over at Forest Elementary School shows you what he is doing! #FPSSuccess #FPSbettertogether
shared_text:
YOUTUBE.COM
Mr. V Earth Day

Forest Elementary School Parent Organization - Farmington Hills, MI
April 20 at 10:47 PM ·

Wednesday is Earth Day! Please share your photos of what you and your families are doing to save and protect our Earth. There are many ways you can help our planet, to name just a few: turn the water off while brushing your teeth, recycle paper, glass etc. pickup trash, plant flowers, make projects out of recycled material. We can’t wait to see what you come up with. Please upload your photos to Mr V’s photo gallery or put in the comments of this post. Here is a link for what Mr. V’s Earth day project is: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a9BB7Svfbzw
